Package: athena-dhcpd
Version: {{VERSION}}
Section: net
Priority: optional
Architecture: {{ARCH}}
Maintainer: Josh Finlay <josh@athenanetworks.com.au>
Homepage: https://github.com/JoshFinlayAU/athena-dhcpd
Description: RFC-compliant DHCPv4 server with conflict detection and HA
 athena-dhcpd is a high-performance DHCPv4 server written in Go with
 built-in ARP/ICMP conflict detection, active-standby high availability,
 dynamic DNS integration, event hooks (scripts + webhooks), and an
 embedded React web management UI.
 .
 Features include full DHCP option support, relay agent (option 82)
 handling, IP conflict detection via ARP/ICMP probing before every
 offer, dynamic DNS integration (BIND, Knot, PowerDNS, Technitium,
 Windows DNS, CoreDNS), lease event hooks, Prometheus metrics, and
 DNS proxy with dynamic blocklists.
Depends: adduser, libc6, libcap2-bin
Recommends: systemd
Suggests: prometheus
